The paper discusses a class of n-player games that are commonly used in machine learning, such as GANs and adversarial training. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions game theory and optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses applications in computer vision (e.g., GANs), which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the use of first-order methods, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
